                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./674:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-10T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 10, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. The representative of the Pan American-Grace Airways has just informed me
                    that the President of Argentina signed their contract yesterday afternoon and
                    that the first airplane carrying mail from Buenos Aires to the United States
                    will leave here the morning of October 12th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
